Born in 88

Climbed trees with no ropes or harness, old Mans Truck had the pop out window that was the air conditioner, played hide and seek, best spot was in the culvert pipe under the road. Horseshoes in the back yard all night under brightness of construction work lights. Club houses and forts in the woods. Fishing all summer long every day. Riding bikes everywhere we wanted to go. Cussing got you a mouth full of soap. Rain hitting the awning of the tin roof. B.B. gun and daddy’s beer can. Wish I was 8 years old again

Brings back memories. My dad and I rode together in his pick up truck over many years. We had a lot of great conversations, and used to listen to Brenda Lee, Dolly, Buck Owens, Johnny Cash, Mel Tillis, Glenn Campbell, Reba, Loretta, and more. I sure miss those times with my dad. My dad could really whistle well (in tune). I miss simple times and wonderful music that told stories. This new song of Blake’s takes me “home”.
